===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbəʊd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abode.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|əʊd}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ang}} ''[[abad]]'', ''[[abood]]'', from {{term|abiden||to abide}}. See ''[[abide]]''. For the change of vowel, compare ''abode'', imp. of ''abide''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} Act of [[waiting]]; delay.
#* And with her fled away without '''abode'''. - [[w:Edmund Spenser|Edmund Spenser]]
# {{uncommon|_|outside fixed expressions}} Stay or [[continuance]] in a place; [[sojourn]].
#* He waxeth at your '''abode''' here. - [[w:Henry Fielding|Henry Fielding]]
# {{formal}} A residence, [[dwelling]] or [[habitation]].
#* Come, let me lead you to our poor '''abode'''. - [[w:William Wordsworth|William Wordsworth]]

